<div type="protocol"><div type="agenda_item" xml:id="top_MRP-3-0-08-2-19181001-P-0248_1"><head><label><num n="1">I. </num></label> Ankündigung eines Friedensschrittes der verbündeten Mächte</head><p>[I.] <tei:index xmlns:p="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/patternmatcher" xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><term type="lvl1">Friedensschluss<term type="lvl2">Amerika, Vereinigte Staaten von</term></term></tei:index>Der <tei:rs xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" ref="#mpr4438" type="person" subtype="talking-minister"><hi rend="#letterspaced">Ministerpräsident</hi></tei:rs> teilt mit, es sei zwischen den <rs ref="#mpr1423" type="place" subtype="multi-ref">verbündeten Mächten</rs> ein Einvernehmen in der Richtung zustande gekommen, dass in gleichzeitigen Noten an den Präsidenten <rs type="person" ref="#mpr10632">Wilson</rs> diesem gegenüber der Wunsch zum Ausdrucke gebracht werde, auf der vom <rs xml:space="preserve" type="person" ref="#mpr10632">Präsidenten</rs> in seiner Botschaft vom 8. Jänner d. J. und seinen späteren Enunziationen gekennzeichneten Grundlage Friedensverhandlungen einzuleiten<note type="footnote" n="1" target="#fn_MRP-3-0-08-2-19181001-P-0248_1"><hi rend="italic">Die 14 Punkte <rs type="person" ref="#mpr10632">Woodrow Wilsons</rs> v. 8. 1. 1918 in</hi> <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"0jSWX8Rs","properties":{"formattedCitation":"{\\scaps {\\scaps Rudin}}, Armistice 1918, 400\\uc0\\u8211{}403.","plainCitation":"Rudin, Armistice 1918, 400–403.","noteIndex":1},"citationItems":[{"id":44480,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/2042149/items/STPWMH38"],"itemData":{"id":44480,"type":"book","call-number":"U-476","edition":"2","event-place":"New Haven, CT","language":"eng","number-of-pages":"vii+442","publisher":"Yale University Press","publisher-place":"New Haven, CT","source":"search.obvsg.at","title":"Armistice 1918","title-short":"Armistice 1918","author":[{"family":"Rudin","given":"Harry R."}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["1948"]]},"citation-key":"rudinArmistice19181948"},"locator":"400–403","label":"page"}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?><bibl>Rudin</bibl>, Armistice 1918, 400–403<title xml:space="preserve">, </title><hi rend="italic">sowie </hi> <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"aa8nehm5m1","properties":{"formattedCitation":"56 {\\scaps Cong. Rec.} 679\\uc0\\u8210{}681 (1918) (Address of the President of the United States); 56 {\\scaps Cong. Rec.} 1951\\uc0\\u8210{}1953 (1918) (Address of the President).","plainCitation":"56 Cong. Rec. 679‒681 (1918) (Address of the President of the United States); 56 Cong. Rec. 1951‒1953 (1918) (Address of the President).","noteIndex":120},"citationItems":[{"id":48264,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/2042149/items/K7A9SRCA"],"itemData":{"id":48264,"type":"book","archive_location":"MRP","call-number":"Zitierweise https://guides.library.cornell.edu/c.php?g=134360&p=8087767","event-place":"Washington","language":"eng","license":"Text is government work; issued: \"1873–\"","publisher-place":"Washington","title":"Congressional Record","title-short":"Cong. Rec.","URL":"https://www.congress.gov/bound-congressional-record/1918/02/11/house-section","accessed":{"date-parts":[["2024",9,12]]},"citation-key":"CongressionalRecord"},"label":"page","prefix":"56 ","suffix":" 679‒681 (1918) (Address of the President of the United States)"},{"id":48264,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/2042149/items/K7A9SRCA"],"itemData":{"id":48264,"type":"book","archive_location":"MRP","call-number":"Zitierweise https://guides.library.cornell.edu/c.php?g=134360&p=8087767","event-place":"Washington","language":"eng","license":"Text is government work; issued: \"1873–\"","publisher-place":"Washington","title":"Congressional Record","title-short":"Cong. Rec.","URL":"https://www.congress.gov/bound-congressional-record/1918/02/11/house-section","accessed":{"date-parts":[["2024",9,12]]},"citation-key":"CongressionalRecord"},"label":"page","prefix":"56 ","suffix":" 1951‒1953 (1918) (Address of the President)"}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?><title>56 <bibl>Cong. Rec.</bibl> 679‒681 (1918) (Address of the President of the United States); 56 <bibl>Cong. Rec.</bibl> 1951‒1953 (1918) (Address of the President). Address of President Wilson, Opening the Campaign for the Fourth Liberty Loan, Delivered at the Metropolitan Opera House in New York City, September 27, 1918</title>, <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"amkmj6c313","properties":{"formattedCitation":"{\\scaps Papers Relating to the Foreign Relations of the US, 1918, 1/I}, Document 258.","plainCitation":"Papers Relating to the Foreign Relations of the US, 1918, 1/I, Document 258.","noteIndex":120},"citationItems":[{"id":48265,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/2042149/items/Y3ESVJT4"],"itemData":{"id":48265,"type":"book","archive_location":"MPR","event-place":"Washington, DC","publisher":"Government Printing Office","publisher-place":"Washington, DC","title":"Papers Relating to the Foreign Relations of the United States, 1918","title-short":"Papers Relating to the Foreign Relations of the US, 1918, 1/I","URL":"https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1918Supp01v01/d258","volume":"Supplement 1, The World War, Volume I","accessed":{"date-parts":[["2024",9,12]]},"issued":{"date-parts":[["1933"]]},"citation-key":"PapersRelatingForeign1933"},"label":"page","suffix":", Document 258"}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?><title>Papers Relating to the Foreign Relations of the US, 1918, 1/I, Document 258.</title></note>. Indem der sprechende Minister seinen Kollegen hievon in streng vertraulicher Weise Kenntnis gebe, möchte er in diesem Augenblicke von welthistorischer Bedeutung das Gelöbnis unwandel<tei:pb xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/>barer Liebe und Treue für die Ah. Dynastie und das teure alte Österreich im eigenen Namen und in dem der Gesamtregierung erneuern. Der Ministerrat schließt sich dieser Kundgebung an<note type="footnote" n="2" target="#fn_MRP-3-0-08-2-19181001-P-0248_2"><hi rend="italic">Die Note des deutschen Reichskanzlers </hi><rs type="person" ref="#mpr16593"><hi rend="italic">Max Prinz v. Baden</hi></rs><hi rend="italic"> an den Präsidenten der <rs type="place" ref="#mpr1463">Vereinigten Staaten</rs> <rs type="person" ref="#mpr10632">Woodrow Wilson</rs> v. 6. 10. 1918 abgedruckt in</hi> <bibl>Wiener Zeitung (A)</bibl> <ref target="http://anno.onb.ac.at/cgi-content/anno?aid=wrz&amp;datum=19181007&amp;seite=1&amp;zoom=33"><hi rend="Book_Title">v. 7. 10. 1918</hi></ref>.<hi rend="italic" xml:space="preserve"> Fortsetzung des Punktes im <ref type="protocol-link" target="toc.html?collection=editions#myTable=f19181007" ana="prot0 top1">MR. v. <date when="1918-10-07">7. 10. 1918</date>/I</ref>.</hi></note>.</p>
